INSERT INTO `news` (`id`,`date`,`category`,`user_id`,`caption`,`text`,`active`,`sort_index`)
VALUES
	(7,'2008-06-16','release_info',1,'Updates to the Career Pathways Web Tool','**The Web Tool received a scheduled maintenance and feature upgrade Monday, June 16, 2008**, addressing how drawings are copied and deleted in the system, as well as adding the ability for persons affiliated with Oregon schools and businesses to apply for an account online. \r\n\r\nFor detailed step-by-step instructions on all Web Tool features, please refer to our online [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Tutorials Tutorials]. \r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nThe Web Tool drawing tools now offers \"**print this version**\", which will render roadmap drawings as an HTML page, where you can print direct from your browser. For step-by-step instructions please visit our online tutorial - [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings_-_Print_This_Version Print This Version]. \r\n\r\nTo **print to PDF** (an maintain active hyperlinks in your roadmap drawing), please email our **Help Desk** by clicking the link for **Help** in our Resources section to the left. Please include your \'\'name\'\', \'\'organization\'\', \'\'drawing title\'\' and drawing \'\'version number\'\' in your request.\r\n',1,0),
	(8,'2010-08-19','welcome',1,'Welcome to the Career Pathways Web Tool','We\'re glad you are here!\r\n\r\n**What Are Roadmap Drawings?**\r\nCareer Pathways Roadmaps are visual tools (or drawings) providing Oregon students and high school and community college advisors/counselors to learn about options and opportunities to navigate their own education and career plans and choices.  Each Roadmap includes common information elements and follows standards so that all\r\nRoadmaps have a similar look across the State of Oregon.\r\n\r\n**What Are POST Drawings?**\r\nPOST stands for Plan of Study Templates. POST Drawings is the newest feature of the Web Tool developed to map high school and community college plans of study together.\r\n\r\n**What is the Web Tool?**\r\nThe Web Tool is a technical tool to provide \"layers\" of information (through Roadmap and POST drawings) that students need to know in order to plan their education and career. This information includes: courses, occupations, wages, competencies or skills, certificates, degrees, credentials, articulation agreements, etc. \r\n\r\n**What You Can Do as a User of the Web Tool!**\r\nAs a user of the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool you will be able to develop, collaborate, track, edit, copy and publish Career Pathways Roadmap and POST drawings to your organization\'s website. \r\n\r\nFor questions, technical assistance, or training needs please email [mailto:helpdesk@ctepathways.org helpdesk@ctepathways.org] and we will get back to you by the next business day.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**About the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool Development Project**\r\n\r\nThe Oregon Department of Community Colleges and Workforce Development (OCCWD) working in partnership with Oregon\'s 17 community colleges through the Oregon Pathways Alliance developed the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool to provide visual maps using web technology for students and citizens to learn more about education, training, occupations, careers, and the labor market in Oregon.\r\n\r\nWe welcome others state agencies, educational institutions, and organizations to [http://oregon.ctepathways.org/p/licensing download the source code] to develop a comparable Web Tool for the students and citizens in their state or region. The Web Tool was developed with funds from the US Department of Labor Employment and Training Administration (US DOL ETA) and the Oregon Community College Strategic Reserve Fund.\r\n\r\n**Oregon Career Pathway Statewide Initiative**\r\n\r\nFor more information about the Oregon Career Pathway Initiative go to:\r\n[http://www.worksourceoregon.org/index.php/career-pathways www.oregonpathways.org]\r\nor contact:\r\nMimi Maduro\r\nPathways Initiative Statewide Director\r\nDept. of Community Colleges & Workforce Development\r\n[mailto:mmaduro@cgcc.cc.or.us mmaduro@cgcc.cc.or.us]',1,0),
	(9,'2009-08-13','ada',1,'ADA/504 Accessibility for Roadmaps','The Web Tool has undergone a series of recent changes that have been aimed in part at ensuring **Accessibility**. Roadmaps are now drawn using Canvas libraries, enabling cross-browser compatibility, better layout control, and printing/PDF capabilities. \r\n\r\n//**The primary features that have been added include:**//\r\n\r\n# Roadmap data available in XML format\r\n# Explicit connections between boxes in maps (versus just graphical lines)\r\n# Text-only version link available for viewing and navigation of roadmaps\r\n# Cross-browser compatibility\r\n# Font sizes easily increased/decreased\r\n# Printing/PDF generation enabled\r\n\r\nThese features directly meet current accessibility requirements and also provide page designers with the means to make their pages accessible for maps created using the current map features. A summary of applicable accessibility features is provided by the [http://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG20/quickref/ W3C Web Accessibility Initiative]:\r\n\r\n* //**Text Alternatives**//: Provide text alternatives for any non-text content so that it can be changed into other forms people need, such as large print, braille, speech, symbols or simpler language\r\n* //**Adaptable**//: Create content that can be presented in different ways (for example simpler layout ) without losing information or structure\r\n* //**Distinguishable**//: Make it easier for users to see and hear content including separating foreground from background \r\n* //**Keyboard Accessible**//: Make all functionality available from a keyboard \r\n* //**Navigable**//: Provide ways to help users navigate, find content and determine where they are \r\n* //**Readable**//: Make text content readable and understandable \r\n* //**Predictable**//: Make Web pages appear and operate in predictable ways \r\n* //**Compatible**//: Maximize compatibility with current and future user agents, including assistive technologies\r\n\r\nRead more about maintaining compliance and viewing Career Pathways roadmaps in accessible formats through our [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings#ADA.2F504_Accessibility_Compliance ADA/504 Accessibility Compliance Tutorial].\r\n',1,1),
	(10,'2010-07-14','tutorial',1,'Online Tutorials','Guided step-by-step instructions on all Web Tool features, covering everything from \"My Account\" to \"Embedding Published Roadmap Drawings\" and \"POST Views\". This is managed and maintained by the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool developers, Sivecki & Associates, LLC. \r\n\r\n**Please click here to access these online training resources:** http://tutorial.ctepathways.org/tutorial\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nTo view **examples of embedded Roadmap Drawings** on many of Oregon\'s Community College \"Career Pathways\" websites, click here: http://tutorial.ctepathways.org/Live_Roadmap_Examples',1,3),
	(11,'2010-01-01','release_info',1,'Summary of Release Notes','An archive of release notes for upgrades to the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool since version 1.0 was released in Oregon, January 2008: [http://cpwebtool.org/Release_Notes CPWebTool.org/Release Notes]',1,0),
	(13,'2010-11-04','dashboard',1,'Feature: Print to PDF!','The Web Tool now offers **Print to PDF** features!\r\n\r\nFrom the Drawing Properties page for Roadmaps and POST Drawings, as well as POST Views, you can now download automatically generated PDF documents of your published drawings! You also have access to a URL link that you can put on your website for viewers to download the same document. This PDF link will always generate a PDF of the most currently published version, rendered identical to your embedded drawings or published HTML links. \r\n\r\nLearn more about the feature here: [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Print_To_PDF http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Print_To_PDF]. \r\n\r\n\r\n',1,1),
	(14,'2008-08-27','release_info',1,'Version 2.3 Web Tool Upgrades','**The Web Tool received a feature upgrade Wednesday, August 27, 2008**. Features and improvements include:\r\n\r\n* All references to \"School\", whether in the main navigation, Drawing list filter, or Users section have been updated to read **Organization** (i.e. \"Organization Colors\", previously \"School Colors\"). This has been done to keep the Web Tool flexible for working with not only Oregon schools, but State organizations and businesses as well. \r\n* The display prior to login and after log in has been updated to reflect our new **Dashboard**, which replaces the previous \"Site News\" section of the Web Tool. \r\n* With this Dashboard update, you will now have access to the //Tutorial, Release Info, ADA Compliance// information, and //Help// feature while logged out of the Web Tool. \r\n* While logged in to the Web Tool these links can now be found in our **Resources** section, underneath the main navigation, at all times. \r\n* As before, the Dashboard will continue to display our \"Welcome...\" message and pertinent information relating to updates to the Web Tool and highlighted features, however you will now find a **Quick Links** section on the Dashboard that provides links to: \r\n * **Add a User** (available to //State Admin, School Admin,// and //Webmaster// users only) \r\n * **Report a Bug** (online form/email), and \r\n * **Request a Feature** (online form/email). \r\n* Guest users can **Apply for an Account** through the Quick Links section found within the **Guest Login**.\r\n * If you have a staff member that you wish to explore the Web Tool, have them demo the site through the Guest Login, and Apply for an Account with your organization. \r\n\r\nFor detailed step-by-step instructions on all Web Tool features, please refer to our **Tutorial** resources. For questions, technical assistance, or training needs please use our online **Help** form to submit your inquiry, and we will get back to you by the next business day.',1,0),
	(15,'2008-03-05','release_info',1,'Version 2.0 Web Tool Upgrades','**A Web Tool update was released March 7th, 2008** that addressed printing and publishing roadmaps. As you continue working in the Web Tool, please keep these things in mind:\r\n\r\n* **Printing Drawings**: If extensive printing needs to be done before March 7th, please email **Help** to request printable files of your roadmaps.\r\n\r\n* **Publishing/Embedding Drawings**: If you need to publish roadmaps to public websites prior to March 7th, please refer to //Publishing Drawings// in the Getting Started Tutorial for instructions; or email **Help** for additional assistance. \r\n\r\n* **Editing School Colors**: School Admin and Webmaster users, please use caution when deleting colors for your school. Changes to school colors are saved immediately. If existing drawings have objects using a deleted color that object will revert to grey/black in color, and a new color will need to be set for that object. Please review your schools drawings before deleting colors. \r\n\r\n',1,0),
	(16,'2010-07-01','help',1,'Roadmap Drawing Canvas Help','<a name=\"General\"></a><h2>General</h2>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Right-click the drawing canvas for a menu to add new objects to the drawing canvas, or change default grid settings.</li>\r\n		<li>Right-click an object for a menu of customizing options.</li>\r\n		<li><b>Change an object\'s color</b> by selecting it and clicking a color from the <var>TOOLS</var> color palette, or using <var>Color</var> on the menu.</li>\r\n\r\n		<li><b>To delete an object</b>, first select it, then hit the <kbd>DELETE</kbd> key on your keyboard, or select <var>Delete</var> from the object\'s menu.</li>\r\n                \r\n                <li><b>To edit the drawing title</b>, click on <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/cog.png\" alt=\"\"/> (Drawing Properties) in the <var>VERSION</var> menu to \"edit\" the Occupation/Program name. Make any necessary change to the name and click \"save\" when finished.</li>\r\n\r\n                <li><b>To assign an Oregon Skill Set category</b>, click on <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/cog.png\" alt=\"\"/> (Drawing Properties) in the <var>VERSION</var> menu. Select the appropriate Oregon Skill Set category from the drop-down box. Upon returning to the drawing canvas the Oregon Skill Set will be displayed under the Roadmap Drawing title bar. Adjustments to your layout/design may be required.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Drawing Canvas Print Frame</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Visible in \"draft\" mode only, these non-printable gray borders provide a visual guide for fitting your Roadmap design to a printer friendly portrait print layout.</li>\r\n<li>Please note: these are only guides! Always use the Print This Version tool feature to review your work for desired print layout.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"GridSettings\"></a><h2>Drawing Canvas Menu</h2>\r\nRight-click the drawing canvas to access:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n	<b>New Menu</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Adds a new <b>box</b>, <b>line</b>, or <b>arrow</b> to the drawing canvas in the same location that was right-clicked.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Grid</b> â†’ <b>Show Grid</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Turns the show grid feature on or off.</li>\r\n		<li>Default is set to on.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Grid</b> â†’ <b>Snap to Grid</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n\r\n		<li>Turns the snap to grid feature on or off.</li>\r\n		<li>Default is set to on. </li>\r\n		<li>Objects snap to nearest horizontal/vertical grid axis. </li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Grid</b> â†’ <b>Edit</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Opens a pop-up window to edit the grid size of drawing canvas.</li>\r\n		<li>Default is set to 10.</li>\r\n		<li>Type any number to manually change grid size, e.g. 15, 20, 25, etc. </li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Changes to grid settings are not saved, and will return to default settings upon exiting the drawing.</b>\r\n	<br /><br />\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Boxes\"></a><h2>Box Menu</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Right-click the drawing canvas and select <b>New</b> â†’ <b>Box</b> to add a new box object. The box will be added in the same location that was right-clicked.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	Right-click box objects to access:<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>Edit Content</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Opens the box\'s content editor in a pop-up window.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Edit Title</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n\r\n		<li>Enables an in-place text editor for the box\'s title.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Color Menu</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sets the color of the box.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Start Connection Here/End Connection Here</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Draws an arrow between two selected boxes. </li>\r\n		<li>Right-click the starting box to select \"Start Connection Here\"; right-click the ending box to select \"End Connection Here\" from the menu.</li>\r\n		<li>Creates a dynamic connection that moves with the connected boxes as layout changes occur. </li>\r\n		<li>Right-click connection for menu of customizing options.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	\r\n		<b>Duplicate</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n\r\n		<li>Makes an exact copy of box, including all content formatting.</li>\r\n		<li>Offsets new duplicate below original.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	\r\n		<b>Delete</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n\r\n		<li>Permanently deletes the box and removes any connections, after confirmation. </li>\r\n		<li>Can also perform same action by hitting the <kbd>DELETE</kbd> key on your keyboard.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Connections\"></a><h2>Connection Menu</h2>\r\n	Please use Connections for ease of layout adjustments and ADA compliance. Connections can translate the relationship of box objects in text only views of these drawings.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<ul>\r\n<li>Right-click the starting box to select \"Start Connection Here\"; right-click the ending box to select \"End Connection Here\" from the menu.</li>\r\n<li>Creates a dynamic connection that moves with the connected boxes as layout changes occur.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	Right-click box connections to access:<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>Start Point menu</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sets the side of the box the line is drawn from: Top, Bottom, Left or Right.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>End Point menu</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n\r\n		<li>Sets the side of the box the line is drawn to: Top, Bottom, Left or Right.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Orientation menu</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sets the orientation (horizontal or vertical) of the connection from the start point. This option is not available if segment is set to 1 (Direct Line).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Segments menu</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sets the number of segments in the connecting line:</li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>1-Seg Line (Straight)</li>\r\n			<li>1-Seg Line (Diagonal)</li>\r\n			<li>2-Seg Line (\"L\")</li>\r\n			<li>3-Seg Line</li>\r\n\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<li>The default, 1-segment line, may not be visually connected to the end point. Adjust by moving the ending box, or selecting a different segment or orientation option.</li>\r\n		<li>1-Seg Line (Diagonal) creates a diagonal line to the destination box regardless of box position.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Color menu</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sets the color of the connection.</li>\r\n\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Auto Position</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Detects box location to adjoining box, and resets connection to 1-Seg Line (Straight).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Delete</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Permanently removes the connection, after confirmation. </li>\r\n		<li>Can also perform same action by hitting the <kbd>DELETE</kbd> key on your keyboard.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"WhyNoLines\"></a><h2>Line and Arrow Menu</h2>\r\nLines and arrows must be manually aligned with box objects, and are discouraged. These have been removed from the <var>TOOLS</var> menu to transition users into using the Connections feature. \r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease use Connections for ease of layout adjustments and ADA compliance. Connections can translate the relationship of box objects in text only views of these drawings.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Right-click the drawing canvas and select <b>New</b> â†’  <b>Line</b> or <b>New</b> â†’ <b>Arrow</b> to add a line or arrow object. The line or arrow will be added in the same location that was right-clicked.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	Right-click line and arrow objects to access:<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>Color Menu</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Sets the color of the line or arrow.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Duplicate</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n\r\n		<li>Makes an exact copy of the line or arrow.</li>\r\n		<li>Offsets new duplicate below original.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Delete</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Permanently removes the line or arrow, after confirmation. </li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Positioning\"></a><h2>Positioning Objects</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>When selected, boxes, connections, lines and arrows show a blue frame, with a green control point at the start, and a red control point at the end. The object\'s menu can be brought up by right-clicking anywhere within this frame.</li>\r\n		<li>Click and drag the green start point or red end point to vertically or horizontally adjust the starting or ending location.</li>\r\n		<li>Connection start and end points can \"slide\" to any desired location along the <var>TOP</var>, <var>BOTTOM</var>, <var>LEFT</var> and <var>RIGHT</var> edges of box objects.</li>\r\n\r\n		<li>When dragging a box, line or arrow, hold down the <kbd>ALT</kbd> key (<kbd>Option</kbd> on Mac) to move the object without snapping to the grid.</li>\r\n		<li>When dragging a start or end point for a line or arrow, hold down the <kbd>Shift</kbd> key to make the line snap to a vertical or horizontal layout.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"ResizingBoxes\"></a><h2>Resizing Boxes</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>When selected, boxes are highlighted with a blue frame, with left and right blue control points. Click and drag either point to expand/retract box width.</li>\r\n		<li>Box height is determined by content.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"EditingContent\"></a><h2>Editing Box Content</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Right-click a box object and select <b>Edit Content</b>. The box\'s content editor will open in a pop-up window.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<var>Warning</var>: DO NOT copy and paste text from MS Word. Hidden code can cause undesired formatting results, printing issues or glitches that can permanently damage drawings. Please only copy and paste from generic text editors.\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<b>Undo/Redo</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click the undo/redo arrows to undo/redo text and formatting changes. Only able to undo changes made during the current editing session.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Line Spacing</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hit the <var>Enter/Return</var> key on your keyboard to automatically double space your content. This is called <var>paragraph spacing</var>.</li>\r\n<li>To single space, hold down <var><b>SHIFT + Enter/Return</b></var> key for a new single spaced line of content.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Spell Check</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click the <var>ABC check</var> icon to spell check box content. </li>\r\n<li>Errors will be underlined in red. Right-click marked words for suggested corrections.</li>\r\n<li>Select the corrected word, or select \"Ignore Word\" or \"Ignore All\".</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Insert/Edit Hyperlink</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Highlight the text a hyperlink will be created with.</li>\r\n<li>The <var>Insert/Edit Link</var> icon will become active.</li>\r\n<li>Click the <var>Insert/Edit Link</var> icon to open the \"Insert/edit link\" pop-up box.</li>\r\n<li>Provide the link URL. The \"target\" link is set to open in a new window, by default.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: Provide a link title. This will not appear in the content.</li>\r\n<li>Click \"Update\" to save and return to the content editor.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Remove Hyperlink</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Highlight the desired hyperlink. The <var>Unlink</var> icon will become active.</li>\r\n<li>Click the <var>Unlink</var> icon to remove the hyperlink.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Insert Image</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click the <var>Insert Image</var> icon to open the <var>Insert/Edit Image</var> pop-up box.</li>\r\n<li>Provide a URL for an image located online.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: Provide an image description, and customize the alignment, dimensions, border, vertical and horizontal space.</li>\r\n<li>Click \"Insert\" to save and return to the content editor.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Insert/Modify Tables</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Place your cursor in the desired location for the table you wish to add.</li>\r\n<li>Click the <var>Insert Table</var> icon to open the \"Insert/Modify table\" pop-up box.</li>\r\n<li>Change the values for \"Cols\" and \"Rows\" as desired.</li>\r\n<li>Optional: Customize cellpadding, cellspacing, alignment, border, width, height, class and table caption. Explore Advanced tab options.</li>\r\n<li>Click \"Insert\" to save and return to the content editor.</li>\r\n<li>Click on the table to add content the table cells. Use the additional tools that are now active across the toolbar to modify table row and cell properties, merge cells, and insert and remove rows and columns.</li>\r\n<li>Or, click the <var>Insert Table</var> icon again to modify the table layout, make the desired changes, and click \"Update\" to save.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Edit CSS</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click the <var>AA</var> icon to customize inline CSS styling. An \"Edit CSS Style\" pop-up box will appear.</li>\r\n<li>Explore options and click \"Apply\" to see the changes save to your content box.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Edit HTML (Source Code)</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click the <var>HTML</var> icon to open the \"HTML Source Editor\" pop-up box.</li>\r\n<li>Edit HTML code with HTML and CSS as desired, and click \"Update\" to save changes to the content editor.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Locking\"></a><h2>Locking Versions</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>From the <var>TOOLS</var> menu, or <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/wrench.png\" alt=\"\" /> Version Settings <b>Actions</b> menu, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/lock_open.png\" alt=\"\" /> lock this version to prevent changes to a specific version.</li>\r\n<li>This is ideal when you are collaborating on a drawing, or want to compare versions without the risk of making accidental changes, and you are not ready to â€œpublishâ€.</li>\r\n		<li>The <var>TOOLS</var> and <b>Actions</b> menus will automatically update to show that this version is now <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/lock.png\" alt=\"\" /> locked.</li>\r\n		<li>Copy it to a new version to make changes.</li>\r\n		<li>Or, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/report_go.png\" alt=\"\" /> publish this version in the <var>TOOLS</var> menu if no more changes are required to publish it.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Copying\"></a><h2>Copy This Version</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n<li>From the <var>TOOLS</var> menu, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/page_copy.png\" alt=\"\" /> copy this version. A pop-up window will appear.</li>\r\n		<li><b><i>Drawings at Your Organization</i></b></li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Create a <b>New Version</b> to the existing drawing</li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n\r\n				<li>The next available version number will be added in your drawing list.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<li>Create a <b>New Drawing</b> copies the existing drawing into an identical new drawing at your organization, and Version 1 will be created.</li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Edit the new drawing name (Occupation/Program) before hitting â€œOKâ€. </li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<li><b><i>Drawings at Another Organization</i></b></li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>A <b>New Drawing</b> will be created in your organization.</li>\r\n			<li>Edit the new drawing name (Occupation/Program) before hitting â€œOKâ€. </li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n\r\n				<li>The drawing will be added to your drawings list and Version 1 will be created.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	<li>The drawing canvas will refresh with the new version or drawing to begin editing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	<b><i>NOTE:</i></b> If no new drawing name is provided, the original drawing name is used and the word â€œcopyâ€ is appended to the new drawing name by default.<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Printing\"></a><h2>Print This Version</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n<li>From the <var>TOOLS</var> menu, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/printer.png\" alt=\"\" /> print this version to render a Roadmap Drawing for printing from the browser menu. </li>\r\n			<li>Set your browsers print settings to \"print background images\" so that titles of boxes print white over dark colored boxes.</li>\r\n		<li>Select <b>File</b> â†’ <b>print preview</b> to preview your drawing prior to printing, and to ensure it will fit to <b>one (1) page</b>. </li>\r\n		<li>Change the print size/scale from \"Shrink to Fit\" to a fixed percentage if the preview shows an undesired layout.</li>\r\n\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b><i>NOTE:</i></b> For best results, design your Roadmap Drawing to fit to one (1) page in a portrait layout, by keeping all objects within the boundaries of the drawing title bar. The Web Tool does not currently support landscape layout or multi-page printing.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Publishing\"></a><h2>Publishing Drawings</h2>\r\n<ul>	\r\n<li>Published drawings are publicly accessible. If you are ready to embed, or link to, a drawing in a public website, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/report_go.png\" alt=\"\" /> publish this version from the <var>TOOLS</var> menu. This will mark the drawing as published, and prevent changes to the \"published\" version.</li>\r\n<li> Public links to published drawings will always reference the currently published version!</li>\r\n<li>Copy it to a new version to make changes. New versions that are published will be instantly accessible through shared published links.</li>\r\n<li> Visit our online <a href=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/p/tutorial\" target=\"_new\">Tutorial</a> for instructions on \"Embedding Roadmaps\".</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n',1,1000),
	(17,'2010-03-08','help',1,'Roadmap Drawing Canvas Help Index','<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'General\');\">General Features</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Boxes\');\">Adding New Box Objects</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'EditingContent\');\">Editing Box Content</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'EditingContent\');\">Line Spacing</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'EditingContent\');\">Hyperlinks & Spell Checking</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'General\');\">Deleting Objects</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Connections\');\">Connecting Boxes</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'GridSettings\');\">Grid Settings</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Positioning\');\">Positioning Objects</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'ResizingBoxes\');\">Resizing Boxes</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Locking\');\">Locking Versions</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Copying\');\">Copying Versions</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Printing\');\">Printing Versions</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Publishing\');\">Publishing Drawings</a><br /><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'WhyNoLines\');\">Why Have Basic Lines Been Removed from TOOLS?</a><br />\r\n',1,1001),
	(18,'2010-07-01','help',1,'POST Drawing Canvas Help','<a name=\"General\"></a><h2>General</h2>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Table cells, that appear yellow when hovered over, can be edited. Click to edit cell content in pop-up windows. </li>\r\n		\r\n		<li>Right-click main table cells for a menu of quick editing options.</li>\r\n\r\n		<li>Only one hyperlink can be added to each table cell.</li>\r\n                \r\n                <li><b>To edit the drawing title</b>, click on <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/cog.png\" alt=\"\"/> (Drawing Properties) in the <var>VERSION</var> menu to \"edit\" the Occupation/Program name. Make any necessary change to the name and click \"save\" when finished.</li>\r\n\r\n                <li><b>To assign an Skill Set category</b>, click on <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/cog.png\" alt=\"\"/> (Drawing Properties) in the <var>VERSION</var> menu. Select the appropriate Oregon Skill Set category from the drop-down box. Upon returning to the drawing canvas the Oregon Skill Set will be displayed under the Roadmap Drawing title bar.</li>\r\n                \r\n                <li>Any <b>legend symbols</b> used will be automatically displayed under the table. Hit F5 on your keyboard to refresh your screen to see changes to the current version.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Quick\"></a><h2>Quick Editing Options</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n		<li>To easily move content, click, <b>drag-and-drop</b> content from one cell to another.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\nRight-click main table cells to:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n	<b>Cut</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Select <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/cut.png\" alt=\"\" /> Cut from the menu. Content is cut from the cell.</li>\r\n		<li>\r\n		Right-click any cell (blank or with existing content) to paste the cut content.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	\r\n	<b>Copy</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Select <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/page_white_copy.png\" alt=\"\" /> Copy to duplicate content. Content will remain in original cell copied.</li>\r\n		<li>Right-click any cell (blank or with existing content) to paste the copied content.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Paste</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Select <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/page_white_paste.png\" alt=\"\" /> Paste to paste cut or copied cell content.</li>\r\n		<li>Right-click any cell (blank or with existing content) to paste content.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Clear</b>\r\n\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Select <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/page_white_delete.png\" alt=\"\" /> Clear to delete cell content without opening the content pop-up window.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Headers\"></a><h2>High School Headers</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Each high school has a default list of column headers. These settings are managed by the High School Administrator.</li>\r\n		<li>Changes to the default list affect NEW drawings only. Headers in existing drawings  will not change.</li>\r\n		<li>To override default headers in a drawing version, click on the header name. (Each version of a single drawing can have different headers.)</li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>A pop-up window will open to change the <b>Header Description</b>.</li>\r\n			<li>Type the new desired header, and click \"Save\", or \"X\" on the pop-up window to cancel, to return to the drawing.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Header\"></a><h2>Header Notes</h2>\r\n	This is <b>not a default row</b> and must be enabled (included) in the Configure Rows & Cols tool feature. Click the header row at the top of the POST table to assign:<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n	<b>Header Content</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Free type desired content, e.g. program descriptions or overviews, etc.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	<b>Link this Content (Optional)</b>\r\n	<ul>\r\n	<li>Ideal for creating a hyperlink to content or files on external websites.</li>\r\n	<li>Copy and paste a URL address in the provided field. The header notes will become a hyperlink.</li>\r\n	<li>Click \"Save\" to return to the drawing canvas.</li>\r\n       <li><b>NOTE</b>: Unless manually deleted from the row, any content will stay in the header notes row and made visible or hidden depending on whether this box is checked or not in the Configure Rows & Cols feature. <b>Hidden content will copy to new drawings or new versions</b>. </li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"ConfigRowsCols\"></a><h2>Configure Rows & Cols</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n		<li>Warning: Use caution - changes are saved automatically! Click \"Close\", or \"X\" on the pop-up window to return to the drawing.</li>\r\n		<li>Click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/table.png\" alt=\"\" /> configure rows & cols from the <var>TOOLS</var> menu to add:</li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>rows for additional grade years/terms (duplicates are allowed for additional content)</li>\r\n			<li>rows for community college pre-requisite (above terms)</li>\r\n			<li>rows for course electives (below grade years/terms)</li>\r\n			<li>blank rows at the bottom of the table for additional content</li>\r\n<li>include header and footer notes rows</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<li>Click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/arrow_left.png\" alt=\"\" /> to the left of the \"Add Row\" option to instantly add additional rows. The \"Rows in your Drawing\" section will update to display the selected change.</li>\r\n<li>Click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/cross.png\" alt=\"\" /> to delete a row. Change are reflected instantly.</li>\r\n<li>Click <b>Delete Last Column</b> to remove columns one at a time, starting far-right. Changes are instantly shown in the <b>Block Diagram</b> below.</li>\r\n<li>Click <b>Add Column</b> to add columns one at a time, to the far-right side of the table. Changes are instantly shown in the <b>Block Diagram</b> below.</li>\r\n<li>Changes are saved automatically. Click \"Close\", or \"X\" on the pop-up window, to return to the drawing.</li>\r\n\r\n	</ul>\r\n		\r\n<a name=\"Locking\"></a><h2>Locking Versions</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>From the <var>TOOLS</var> menu, or <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/wrench.png\" alt=\"\" /> Version Settings <b>Actions</b> menu, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/lock_open.png\" alt=\"\" /> lock this version to prevent changes to a specific version.</li>\r\n<li>This is ideal when you are collaborating on a drawing, or want to compare versions without the risk of making accidental changes, and you are not ready to â€œpublishâ€.</li>\r\n		<li>The <var>TOOLS</var> and <b>Actions</b> menus will automatically update to show that this version is now <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/lock.png\" alt=\"\" /> locked.</li>\r\n		<li>Copy it to a new version to make changes.</li>\r\n		<li>Or, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/report_go.png\" alt=\"\" /> publish this version in the <var>TOOLS</var> menu if no more changes are required to publish it.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Copying\"></a><h2>Copy This Version</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n<li>From the <var>TOOLS</var> menu, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/page_copy.png\" alt=\"\" /> copy this version. A pop-up window will appear.</li>\r\n		<li><b><i>Drawings at Your Organization</i></b></li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>Create a <b>New Version</b> to the existing drawing</li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n\r\n				<li>The next available version number will be added in your drawing list.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<li>Create a <b>New Drawing</b> copies the existing drawing into an identical new drawing at your organization, and Version 1 will be created.</li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Edit the new drawing name (Occupation/Program) before hitting â€œOKâ€. </li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<li><b><i>Drawings at Another <i>Like</i> Organization</i></b></li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li><i><b>NOTE</b>: High School drawings cannot be copied to a Community College, and Community College drawings cannot be copied to a High School.</i></li>\r\n			<li>A <b>New Drawing</b> will be created in your organization.</li>\r\n			<li>Edit the new drawing name (Occupation/Program) before hitting â€œOKâ€. </li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n\r\n				<li>The drawing will be added to your drawings list and Version 1 will be created.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n		</ul>\r\n		<li><b><i>Drawings at Affiliated High Schools</i></b></li>\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>A Community College or Business Organization user can:\r\n			<ul>\r\n			<li>create a <b>New Drawing</b> or <b>New Version</b> within that \"Affiliated High School\", or</li>\r\n			<li>create a <b>New Drawing</b> at a different, selected \"Affiliated High School\".</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<li>Edit the new drawing name (Occupation/Program) before hitting â€œOKâ€. </li>\r\n			<ul>\r\n\r\n				<li>The drawing will be added to the designated Organization list of drawings and Version 1 will be created.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n		</ul>\r\n\r\n	<li>The drawing canvas will refresh with the new version or drawing to begin editing content.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n	<b><i>NOTE:</i></b> If no new drawing name is provided, the original drawing name is used and the word â€œcopyâ€ is appended to the new drawing name by default.<br />\r\n\r\n	<br />\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Printing\"></a><h2>Print This Version</h2>\r\n	<ul>\r\n<li>From the <var>TOOLS</var> menu, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/printer.png\" alt=\"\" /> print this version to render a POST Drawing for printing from the browser menu. </li>\r\n		<li>Select <b>File</b> â†’ <b>print preview</b> to preview your drawing prior to printing, and to ensure it will fit to <b>one (1) page</b>. </li>\r\n		<li>Change the print size/scale from \"Shrink to Fit\" to a fixed percentage if the preview shows an undesired layout.</li>\r\n\r\n	</ul>\r\n\r\n<a name=\"Publishing\"></a><h2>Publishing Drawings</h2>\r\n<ul>	\r\n<li>Published drawings are publicly accessible. If you are ready to embed, or link to, a drawing in a public website, click <img src=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/common/silk/report_go.png\" alt=\"\" /> publish this version from the <var>TOOLS</var> menu. This will mark the drawing as published, and prevent changes to the \"published\" version.</li>\r\n<li> Public links to published drawings will always reference the currently published version!</li>\r\n<li>Copy it to a new version to make changes. New versions that are published will be instantly accessible through shared published links.</li>\r\n<li> Visit our online <a href=\"http://oregon.ctepathways.org/p/tutorial\" target=\"_new\">Tutorial</a> for instructions on creating \"POST Views\" and \"Embedding POST Views\".</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n',1,2000),
	(19,'2010-07-01','help',1,'POST Drawing Canvas Help Index','<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'General\');\">General Features</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Quick\');\">Quick Editing Options</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Headers\');\">High School Row Headers</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Header\');\">Header Notes</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Footer\');\">Footer Notes</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'ConfigRowsCols\');\">Configure Rows & Cols</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Locking\');\">Locking Versions</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Copying\');\">Copying Versions</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Printing\');\">Printing Versions</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"javascript:showHelp(\'Publishing\');\">Publishing Drawings</a><br />',1,2001),
	(20,'2009-04-15','release_info',1,'Web Tool 3.0 - Major Upgrade','**The Web Tool received major feature upgrades Wednesday, April 15, 2009**. Features and improvements include:\r\n\r\n* Site redesign and incorporation of graphic icons to make tools and features more user-friendly.\r\n* Incorporated the **POST Drawings** feature, which maps high school and community college plans of study.\r\n* Added **Affiliations** for community college users to assist high schools in creating their plan of study templates.\r\n* Added **High School Settings** so that each high school can manage their own list of default column headers.\r\n* Added **POST Views** to create the published \"views\" of mapped POST Drawings.\r\n* **Upgraded content editor** for Roadmap Drawings to allow for **Spell Checking**, **Insert Table**, **Insert Image**, and multiple other new features. \r\n* Improved **HELP menus** throughout the site, and within the Roadmap Drawings and POST Drawings editing pages.\r\n* Improved online **Tutorials** with revised topic layouts and graphics for visual reference. \r\n\r\nFor detailed step-by-step instructions on all Web Tool features, please refer to RESOURCES :: **Tutorial**. \r\n\r\nFor questions, technical assistance, or training needs please use our automated **Help Desk** form to submit your inquiry, and we will get back to you by the next business day.',1,0),
	(21,'2009-06-21','release_info',1,'Version 3.1 Web Tool Upgrades','**The Roadmap Drawings feature of the Web Tool received major feature upgrades Sunday, June 21, 2009**. //POST Drawing features were not affected by this upgrade.//\r\n\r\n**Introduction**\r\nThis upgrade is different than other upgrades with new features and bug fixes. Here\'s why. As Oregon\'s unemployment rate has risen and the number of job seekers has exploded, the need for occupational information has expanded as well. In order to assist job seekers across the state, leaders at our Employment Dept. and Worksource Oregon centers expressed an interest in being able to see Career Pathways Roadmaps by occupational area and not have to search every community college website to find a specific program. To do this, we are now linking all published Career Pathways Roadmaps on the Occupational Report in OLMIS.\r\n\r\nWhen a job seeker or staff person goes into an Occupational report on OLMIS at the top of the page will be a link for \"Career Pathways Roadmaps\". When the user clicks on this link, a list of links of all of the available community college roadmaps will be listed.\r\n\r\n**Benefits**\r\nYour community college roadmaps will now be available on OLMIS giving job seekers around the state the opportunity to learn about your program. The added benefit to you is that prospective students browsing careers options on the OLMIS website will now be able to link to roadmaps for the community colleges offering degree and certification programs in their field of interest. \r\n\r\n**Changes You\'ll See**\r\n* **Standardized roadmap drawing titles.** This has been done to help avoid typographical errors and maintain consistency in the roadmap titles, following the list of approved career and technical education programs in the Oregon Community College Viewbook, January 2009. For instance, we have seen variations in how roadmaps have been named for the EMT program, such as EMT Emergency Tech, Emergency Med Technician, and Emergency Med Technology.\r\n* Where applicable, we have matched roadmaps to the list of Approved Career & Technical Education Program in the Community College Viewbook. The roadmaps are also now also sorted by Oregon Skill Set.\r\n* We recognize that many of your roadmaps are not yet listed in this approved program list, or you may title your program something other than the approved program name. Don\'t worry! If your program fits into an approved program category, you can continue to specify an alternate title, which will be used as the roadmap title, like before. If no alternate title is provided, the approved program name will be used instead. And if your program is \"not listed\" in the approved program name list, you can use the alternate title to state your program name like before. It\'s that simple!\r\n* In addition, through the Drawing Properties screen for your published roadmaps, you can now add **OMLIS links** by either searching your roadmap for URLs you may have added to OLMIS occupational report pages, or by manually adding OMLIS URLs. A simple click on a checkbox next to the desired occupation listing will allow that roadmap to be publicly accessible on the OLMIS website for that occupation.\r\n* **NOTE**: the folks at OLMIS and the Oregon Employment Department are currently finishing up the programming on their end. As soon as that is tested and ready to release, you will get an email letting you know how roadmaps will be displayed.\r\n\r\n**How You Can Help**\r\nAs with any new change, there may be glitches, and we encourage your to check over your roadmaps to ensure the titles look the way you want. And as always, we welcome your input and feedback. Please use our automated **Help Desk** to submit your feedback and questions.\r\n\r\nTutorial revisions specific to this upgrade are for **Roadmap Drawings only**:\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawing_Properties Roadmap Drawing Properties]\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings#Adding_a_New_Drawing Adding a New Drawing]\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings#Renaming_Drawings Renaming Drawings]\r\n* \'\'**NEW**\'\' [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings#Linking_to_OLMIS_Occupational_Reports Linking to OLMIS Occupational Reports]\r\n\r\nFor all other detailed step-by-step instructions on Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool features, please refer to RESOURCES :: **Tutorial**. \r\n',1,0),
	(22,'2010-03-24','release_info',1,'Webinar & On Site Training Sessions','**Webinar Training Conferences**\r\n\r\nContact us to schedule a customized webinar session for your college or school on topics that meet your training needs, and times that work for you.\r\n\r\nEmail us at [mailto:helpdesk@ctepathways.org helpdesk@ctepathways.org].\r\n\r\n\r\n**On Site Training Sessions**\r\n\r\nCustomized, regional, on site training sessions are available upon request for both the Roadmap and POST features. If you are interested in coordinating a training in your area, please contact us at [mailto:helpdesk@ctepathways.org helpdesk@ctepathways.org].\r\n',1,0),
	(24,'2010-03-24','release_info',1,'Version 3.2 Web Tool Upgrades','As of **Tuesday, March 23, 2010** you will see and experience the following updates and improvements to the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool:\r\n\r\n**Bug Fixes**\r\nThank you to everyone who has reported technical issues with the Web Tool. For new software we are fortunate that most of these issues have been minor in the grand scheme of things!\r\n\r\n**POST Drawings**\r\n\r\n* **Drawing List - Organization filter boxes** now correctly displays \"Show All High Schools\" and \"Show All Community Colleges\".\r\n* **Drawing List - High School users** will now see drawings listed for Community Colleges and Organizations that they are affiliated with when clicking **\"Affiliated Drawings\"**.\r\n* **Drawing List - version \"Notes\"** field is now clearing properly. Notes written for any version, in the version settings page, will be displayed in the drawing list. Users can edit or clear notes that no longer apply to a specific version.\r\n* **Content hyperlinks** now open in a new window, by default. \r\n\r\n**Roadmaps Drawings**\r\n\r\n* **Drawing List - version \"Notes\"** field is now clearing properly. Notes written for any version, in the version settings page, will be displayed in the drawing list. Users can edit or clear notes that no longer apply to a specific version.\r\n* **Copying Drawings - Removed secondary copy confirmation window/prompt**. Redundant step.\r\n\r\n**Feature Requests**\r\n\r\n* **Roadmaps - Edit Color Palette**: Organization Administrators and Webmasters can now update colors used in existing roadmaps by replacing an existing color with a new color. This feature is found in \"Organization Colors\" on the side bar, but should be used with discretion!\r\n* **Roadmaps & POST - \"Unpublish\" Drawings**: You now have the ability to \"unpublish\" drawings! Ideal for test drawings, drawings that users don\'t want made public on OLIMS, or programs that are no longer being offered, but should not be deleted. How? From the TOOLS menu on the drawing canvas, click \"unpublish this version\".\r\n* **Community College POST Drawings - Course Credits**: A new field has been added to the content editor for listing the number of course credits. Credits will appear in parenthesis in the table, for example \"(3)\".\r\n\r\nWe appreciate your feedback and thank you for your patience as we have worked hard to implement these changes.\r\n\r\n**Upcoming Features**\r\nRequests that did not make it into the above list are still in development, and will be completed by June 2010. Here is a list of those pending requests:\r\n\r\n* **Roadmaps - Drawing Canvas Print Frame**: Adding a non-printable printing guide (or frame) on the drawing canvas grid to assist users in design layout for optimal printing.\r\n* **Roadmap & POST Drawings Lists - Retain Keyword Search Results**: Retain keyword search text so that when a user returns to the drawing list they do not have to re-enter their search query.\r\n* **OLMIS Occupational Reports - Links**: Updating OLMIS to link directly to roadmaps on college web pages instead of linking to Web Tool. Keeps viewers on \"branded\" community college web pages, where their roadmaps are being embedded.\r\n* **POST - Additional Legend Symbols**: Adding \"AP\" for Advanced Placement. We are not implementing course specific descriptions at this time.\r\n* **POST  - Community College Header Field**: Similar to the footer, except to be added to the top of the table underneath the college name, before the Prerequisites row. This is to allow community college users to add notes, a brief introductory or description, to a Community College POST drawing before the course information is listed.\r\n\r\nWe welcome your additional feedback regarding these issues, or new requests. Please email our Technical Support team at [mailto:helpdesk@ctepathways.org helpdesk@ctepathways.org].\r\n\r\nTutorial revisions specific to this upgrade are available here:\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Organization_Colors#Delete_or_Reassign_Colors Delete or Reassign Colors]\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Unpublish_This_Version Unpublish This Version]\r\n\r\nFor all other detailed step-by-step instructions on Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool features, please refer to the online [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial Tutorial].',1,0),
	(25,'2010-01-11','release_info',1,'Upcoming Bug Fixes & Feature Requests','Thank you to everyone who has reported technical issues and feature requests for the Web Tool. Our development committee has recently approved many pending issues and requests and we are now in development to implement the following:\r\n\r\n**Bug Fixes**\r\n\r\n* **POST Drawings List - Organization filter box** not working properly for \"All High Schools\" or \"All Community Colleges\".\r\n* **POST Drawings** - Set **content hyperlinks** to open in a new window, by default.\r\n* **POST Drawings - \"Affiliated Drawings\"** feature to be corrects so that High School users will see Community College and Organizations that they are affiliated with.\r\n* **Roadmap & POST Drawings Lists - Fix version \"Notes\" field** to clear properly. Notes can be written for any version, in the version settings page, but are not currently clearing/deleting properly.\r\n* **Copying Drawings - Remove secondary copy confirmation window/prompt.** Redundant step.\r\n\r\n**Feature Requests**\r\n\r\n* **Roadmaps - Edit Color Palette**: When changing a school\'s colors (in \"Organization Colors\") users will be able to updated colors used in existing roadmaps by dynamically replacing an existing color with a new color.\r\n* **Roadmaps - Drawing Canvas Print Frame**: Adding a non-printable printing guide (or frame) on the drawing canvas grid to assist users in design layout for optimal printing.\r\n* **Roadmap & POST Drawings Lists - Retain Keyword Search Results**: Retain keyword search text so that when a user returns to the drawing list they do not have to re-enter their search query.\r\n* **Roadmaps & POST - \"Unpublish\" Drawings**: Adding ability to \"unpublish\" drawings. Ideal for test drawings, drawings that users don\'t want made public on OLIMS, or programs that are no longer being offered, but should not be deleted.\r\n* **POST - Course Credits**: Add a field in the content editor for number of course credits. Credits will appear in parenthesis in the table, for example \"(3)\".\r\n* **POST - Additional Legend Symbols**: Adding \"AP\" for Advanced Placement. We are not implementing course specific descriptions at this time.\r\n* **POST  - Community College Header Field**: Similar to the footer, except to be added to the top of the table underneath the college name, before the Prerequisites row. This is to allow community college users to add notes, a brief introductory or description, to a Community College POST drawing before the course information is listed.\r\n* **OLMIS Occupational Reports - Links**: Updating OLMIS to link directly to roadmaps on college web pages instead of linking to Web Tool. Keeps viewers on \"branded\" community college web pages, where their roadmaps are being embedded.\r\n\r\n**We will notify you as we update the Web Tool with these fixes, enhancements and new features!**\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nAs much as we would like to implement all of your requests immediately, budget and prioritization restraints prevent us from being able to do it all now. We thank you for your patience and appreciate your feedback. Requests that did not make it into the above list are pending approval for development later in the year, in our 2010-2011 budget. Here is a list of those the pending requests:\r\n\r\n**Projected 2010-2011 Budget Items**\r\n\r\n* **Roadmaps - New Drawing Features**: Add \"background container\" style object that can be given a solid color for object layering; add object layering to improve design and allow connections to overlap boxes; add connection line styles such as dotted or gradient lines and fat arrows; add free type text box (without borders) to create floating text.\r\n* **Roadmaps - Grid Settings**: Save grid settings as a user preference.\r\n* **POST - Custom Row Titles**: Add capacity to select from pre-determined alternatives to row titles.\r\n * Current row titles default to \"1st Year Fall\", \"1st Year Winter\", \"Electives\", \"Prerequisites\", etc. \r\n *  Request to choose alternate rows titles without seasons such as \"Term 1\", \"Term 2\", etc. \"Gen. Ed\". \r\n * \"Requirements\" (different than \"Prerequisites\"), \"Core Requirements\", etc. \r\n * Allow Organizations to set defaults for these choices for new drawings.\r\n* **POST - \"Preview\" Configure Table Changes**: Edit \"Configure Rows & Tables\" to allow preview of changes before automatically changing database table structure. Allow \"save\" or \"cancel\" before returning to POST drawing.\r\n* **POST - Copy Content Between Drawings**: Add the ability to copy tables contents from one drawing and paste them in to another.\r\n* **POST - Affiliations**: Add capability of \"Other Organizations\" to be affiliated with Community Colleges and High Schools in order to complete POST Views using drawings from both organization types.\r\n* **Most Visited Drawings**: a new sidebar feature that would highlight the most recent drawings that have been accessed. Feature to be defined.\r\n* **Users List - Filtering/Search Criteria**: Update users page with basic filtering/searching features to allow users to find other users more easily.\r\n* **User Discussion Board**: pending feedback from users. This would be a Q&A forum with categories that will become a knowledge base for users to research issues and post items for discussion/sharing between other users.\r\n* **Print to PDF**: Automatically generate PDFs of Roadmaps and POST Drawings to bypass the manual step of printing to PDF from the browser.\r\n\r\nWe welcome your additional feedback regarding these issues, or new requests. Please email us at [mailto:helpdesk@ctepathways.org helpdesk@ctepathways.org]. ',1,0),
	(26,'2010-07-01','release_info',1,'Version 3.3 Web Tool Upgrades','As of **Thursday, July 1, 2010** you will see and experience the following updates and improvements to the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool:\r\n\r\n**Bug Fixes**\r\nThank you to everyone who has reported technical issues with the Web Tool. For new software we are fortunate that most of these issues have been minor in the grand scheme of things!\r\n\r\n**--Roadmap & POST Drawing Lists--**\r\n* **Occupations/Programs filter boxes** now function properly when program names are selected. New improvements include a \"loading\" graphics display while the drawing list is generating after filter selections are made, and the ability to click \"show all\" from the organizations filter box to change selection of organizations.\r\n* Words typed in to the **keyword search** field are now retained so that when a user leaves and returns to the drawing list they do not have to re-do their search query.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Feature Requests**\r\nWe thank you for your patience as we have worked hard to implement your requests, and we welcome your additional feedback regarding these issues, or new requests. Please email us at [mailto:helpdesk@ctepathways.org helpdesk@ctepathways.org].\r\n\r\n**--Roadmap & POST Drawing Lists--**\r\n* **Drawing versions are now listed in reverse (descending) order** so that the most recent version is at the top of the list, and more easily accessible.\r\n\r\n\r\n**--Roadmap Drawings--**\r\n* **Drawing Canvas Print Frame** is now a part of the drawing canvas during Roadmap development. Visible in \"draft\" mode only, these non-printable gray borders provide a visual guide for fitting your design to a printer friendly portrait print layout. Please note: these are only guides! Always use the Print this Version tool feature to review your work for desired print layout.\r\n* **Color Palettes** have been updated to include \"white (#ffffff)\" as a standard color selection for all organizations. Some users have been using this color to creating floating box effects in their drawings.\r\n* **Drawing Properties** pages now provide an **External Link** reference based on where an individual Roadmap is embedded. If an external link is detected for your organization, this link will be used by OLIMS to direct traffic to your Roadmaps and organization website (instead of viewing Roadmaps off of the Web Tool server). This External Link feature can be found directly under the embed code of published drawings.\r\n* **Drawing Properties** pages now provide a list of **Embed Views** (at the bottom of the page) as a reference to how many sites are embedding a particular Roadmap, and how many views it has received since being embedded.\r\n\r\n\r\n**--POST Drawings--**\r\n* **POST Drawings** now offer an optional row **header notes** field (similar to the existing footer row) at the top of POST drawing tables where general program notes and external hyperlinks can be added. Both the \"header notes\" and \"footer notes\" rows can be included (displayed or hidden) by checkbox toggle in the configure rows & cols feature, however the footer row is displayed by default.\r\n* **AP - Advanced Placement** has been added as a new POST Legend Symbol option.\r\n\r\n**Upcoming Features**\r\nOur design committee is meeting in July to review pending feature requests and prioritize development for the coming 2010-2011 development year. We will get back to you on approved requests and our timeline for development.\r\n\r\nTutorial revisions specific to this upgrade are available here:\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawing_Properties#If_the_Roadmap_Drawing_is_Published Roadmap Drawing Properties - If Published]\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings#Drawing_Canvas_Print_Frame Drawing Canvas Print Frame]\r\n* [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Organization_POST_Drawings#Header_Row_.28aka_Header_Notes.29 Header Notes] (See also: Footer Notes, Configure Rows & Cols)\r\n\r\nFor all other detailed step-by-step instructions on Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool features, please refer to the online [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial Tutorial].',1,0),
	(27,'2010-11-04','release_info',1,'Version 3.4 Web Tool Upgrades','As of **Friday, November 5, 2010** you will see and experience the following updates and improvements to the Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool:\r\n\r\n**New Features**\r\n* **Roadmap Drawings, POST Views & POST Drawings - Print to PDF**: From the Drawing Properties page for Roadmaps and POST Drawings, as well as POST Views, you can now download automatically generated PDF documents of your published drawings! You also have access to a URL link that you can put on your website for viewers to download the same document. This PDF link will always generate a PDF of the most currently published version, rendered identical to your embedded drawings or published HTML link. **Read more here:** http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Print_To_PDF\r\n\r\n* **Improved External Links to OLMIS & MyPathCareers.org**: We are able to track links to embedded Roadmap Drawings and POST Views when you place the embed code (found in your Drawing Properties page) in your website. If the Web Tool detects an external link we are able to share that link with outside resources such as OLMIS and MyPathCareers.org, to direct outside traffic to your community college pathways websites! The improvements to this feature are in determining which link we share. If we detect multiple links (listed under \"Embed Views\" in your Drawing Properties page), you can now choose which external link you want as the \"primary\" URL. Or, you can simply copy and paste your preferred URL in the External Link field and save your changes. **Read more here**: http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawing_Properties#How_to_Edit_an_External_Link\r\n\r\n* **POST  Views & POST Drawings - Printing Legend Symbols**: Legend symbols are now drawn in an image tag instead of as a background image. This makes them print by default. End viewers are no longer dependent on enabling \"print background images\" with their browsers print settings to print correctly. \r\n\r\n**Bug Fixes**\r\n* **Published Roadmap Drawings - Links to OLMIS**: OLMIS uses two different domains for their full occupational reports. This has been causing a conflict in registering some links for published roadmaps since some users copy the second link format show below (olmis.emp.state.or.us). The Web Tool was original setup to only recognize the first domain shown below (qualityinfo.org). With this fix the Web Tool now supports both domains.\r\n * http://qualityinfo.org/olmisj/OIC?areacode=4101000000&rpttype=full&action=report&occ=111021&go=Continue\r\n * http://olmis.emp.state.or.us/olmisj/OIC?areacode=4101000000&rpttype=full&action=report&occ=111021&go=Continue\r\n * **Read more about using correct OLMIS Links here**: http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial/Roadmap_Drawings#Using_the_Correct_OLMIS_Links\r\n\r\n* **POST Drawings - High School Headers**: Added ability to hit enter on keyboard to save changes to High School POST Drawings column headings.\r\n\r\n* **User Account Profile**: Added the users Organization name to the user profile page, and corrected the drawings list display to reverse the order of versions keeping the most current version at the top of the list.\r\n\r\nWe appreciate your feedback and thank you for your patience as we have worked hard to implement these changes.\r\n\r\n**Upcoming Features**\r\nRequests that did not make it into the above list are still in development, and will be completed in the near future. Here is a list of those pending requests:\r\n\r\n* **POST Drawings - Bug Fix**: Fix additional browser window/tab that is opening when attempting to edit content.\r\n\r\n* **Roadmap & POST Drawing List - Bug Fix**: Fix minor defects in filter box function and results.\r\n\r\n* **POST Drawings - Preview Rows & Columns Configuration Table**: Allow for a preview of table layout changes before saving the changes to the drawing. A new \"Save\" or \"Cancel\" button will be added before returning to the active POST Drawing.\r\n\r\n* **POST Drawings - Alternative Row Titles**: Add capacity to select from pre-determined alternative row titles:\r\n * Current row titles default to \"1st Year Fall\", \"2nd Year Fall\", \"Electives\", \"Prereq\", blank, etc.\r\n * We will be adding an approved list of alternative row titles for users to choose from, such as \"Term 1\", \"Term 2\", etc., \"Gen Ed\", \"Required\", and \"Core Req\"\r\n * \'\'If you have feedback on additional row titles that you would like considered, please submit your suggestions to helpdesk@ctepathways.org for review.\'\'\r\n\r\n* **User Permissions**: \"Org Admin\" and \"Webmaster\" users will be given the capability of adding and editing/managing users for their affiliated high schools.\r\n\r\n* **Affiliations**: \"Other Orgs\" (such as Lane ESD) will be able to add specific Community Colleges to their list of \"Affiliations\" so that they can create POST Views using their local community college\'s POST Drawings.\r\n\r\n----\r\nFor detailed step-by-step instructions on all Career Pathways Roadmap Web Tool features, please refer to our online [http://cpwebtool.org/tutorial Tutorials]. ',1,0);
